cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CV. 

The paper proposes a sample-efficient approach to learning closed-loop policies for nonprehensile manipulation, which involves planning and control in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also leverages reinforcement learning (RL) and proposes a new technique, which suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with control and optimization, which could place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses simulated environments and experiments with a physical manipulator, which could suggest it belongs to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) due to the use of visual perception in robotics.
